webpackJsonp([0xcfb835163855],{428:function(e,t){e.exports={data:{markdownRemark:{html:'<p>I saw a lot of big projects/repositories with hundreds or even thousands of stale branches where nothing really happens.\nUsually, no one cares to clean up all this mess. There is a nice simple GitHub tweak where you can prevent this.</p>\n<h2 id="automatically-delete-merged-branches"><a href="#automatically-delete-merged-branches" aria-hidden="true" class="anchor"><svg aria-hidden="true" height="16" version="1.1" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a>Automatically delete merged branches</h2>\n<p>Github branches can be automatically deleted after press on the merge button.</p>\n<p>You need to be a <strong>repository admin</strong>:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Navigate to repository <strong>Settings</strong></li>\n</ol>\n<p><a href="https://imgur.com/gICbc6V"><img src="https://i.imgur.com/gICbc6Vl.png" title="source: imgur.com"></a></p>\n<ol start="2">\n<li>Scroll down to the <strong>"Merge button"</strong> section</li>\n<li>Activate <strong>Automatically delete head branches</strong> checkbox</li>\n</ol>\n<p><a href="https://imgur.com/Tek0MBm"><img src="https://i.imgur.com/Tek0MBml.png" title="source: imgur.com"></a></p>\n<p>Merged something accidentally and want your branch back? Don\'t worry, you\'ll be able to restore deleted branched.</p>',timeToRead:1,excerpt:"I saw a lot of big projects/repositories with hundreds or even thousands of stale branches where nothing really happens.\nUsually, no oneâ€¦",frontmatter:{title:"How to delete GitHub branches automatically after merge by default",cover:null,date:"2019-11-14",category:"tech",tags:["coding","open source","code","dev","github","dev tools","git"],author:"alex"},fields:{slug:"/how-to-delete-git-hub-branches-automatically-after-merge-by-default"}},prev:{excerpt:"How to invest in ETF? Hi there! Recently I've started to do some research on ETF topic and how I can invest inâ€¦",frontmatter:{title:"Three simple steps to invest in ETF",cover:"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1459257831348-f0cdd359235f?ixlib=rb-0.3.5&ixid=eyJhcHBfaWQiOjEyMDd9&s=7e537922f712f142b24cf9c897f0ab05&auto=format&fit=crop&w=2550&q=80",date:"2018-07-25"},fields:{slug:"/three-simple-steps-to-invest-in-etf"}},next:{excerpt:"Renovate  - is a tool that does automated dependency updates for your project and the nicest thing is that it'sâ€¦",frontmatter:{title:"ðŸ¤– How to configure Renovate - automated dependencies updates for your project",cover:null,date:"2019-11-11"},fields:{slug:"/ðŸ¤–-how-to-configure-renovate-automated-dependencies-updates-for-your-project"}},authors:{edges:[{node:{id:"alex",name:"Alexander Grischuk",image:"https://www.dropbox.com/s/ifvhc39k53udz1e/profile-pic-size.jpg?raw=1",url:"https://www.linkedin.com/in/alxgi/",bio:"Frontend Engineer at Signavio. I like to build apps with React while keeping good UX in mind."}}]}},pathContext:{slug:"/how-to-delete-git-hub-branches-automatically-after-merge-by-default",total:12,prev:"/three-simple-steps-to-invest-in-etf",next:"/ðŸ¤–-how-to-configure-renovate-automated-dependencies-updates-for-your-project"}}}});
